{# gml/recognize-ensemble.j2 - KnowAct: recognize, discriminate, parse #}
{# Purpose: Parse concept into states and ports #}
{# Note: This template is about GML "state ensembles" (a different concept from hKask ensemble). #}
{# The hKask ensemble module was removed 2026-06-14; future multi-agent mode will evolve from dual-presence. #}

{% from 'gml/validate-inputs.j2' import validate_concept %}
{% from 'gml/cns-instrument.j2' import start_span, end_span, record_error, audit_log %}
{% from 'gml/macros.j2' import mwc_state_function, hill_coefficient, partition_function %}

{% set concept = inputs.concept %}
{% set params = inputs.parameters | default({}) %}

{# CNS span start #}
{{ start_span('recognize', concept.id | default('unknown')) }}

{# Validate inputs #}
{% set errors = validate_concept(concept) %}
{% if errors and errors | length > 0 %}
{% include 'gml/error-validation.j2' %}
{{ end_span('recognize', 'error', {'errors': errors | length}) }}
{% else %}

## Allosteric Recognition: {{ concept.name }}

### State Ensemble

This concept dances between two interpretive frames:

| State | Type | Description | Energy |
|-------|------|-------------|--------|
| **T-State** | Conservative | {{ concept.t_state.description }} | {{ concept.t_state.energy }} |
| **R-State** | Progressive | {{ concept.r_state.description }} | {{ concept.r_state.energy }} |

### Default Bias (L)

{% set L = params.l | default(concept.l, 100.0) %}
{% if L > 10 %}
The default bias **L = {{ L }}** strongly favors the T-state (conservative interpretation).
Without contextual pressure, this concept is interpreted conservatively ~{{ (100 / (L + 1)) | round(1) }}% of the time.
{% elif L < 0.1 %}
The default bias **L = {{ L }}** strongly favors the R-state (progressive interpretation).
Without contextual pressure, this concept is interpreted progressively ~{{ (100 / (L + 1)) | round(1) }}% of the time.
{% else %}
The default bias **L = {{ L }}** indicates balanced interpretive flexibility.
The concept has no strong default toward either frame.
{% endif %}

### Allosteric Ports

{% for port in concept.ports %}
**Port {{ loop.index }}: {{ port.name }}**
- Shape: {{ port.effector_shape }}
- Affinity (c): {{ port.affinity_c }}
- {% if port.affinity_c < 1 %}Activator port (favors R-state){% elif port.affinity_c > 1 %}Inhibitor port (favors T-state){% else %}Neutral port{% endif %}
- Bound: {{ port.bound_effector.name if port.bound_effector else "None" }}
{% endfor %}

### Current Equilibrium

{% set alpha = params.alpha | default(concept.current_alpha, 0.0) %}
{% set n = concept.ports | length %}
{% set c_avg = (concept.ports | sum(attribute='affinity_c')) / n if n > 0 else 1.0 %}
{% set r_bar = mwc_state_function(concept.l, c_avg, n, alpha) %}

- Contextual pressure (α): {{ alpha | round(3) }}
- Cooperativity dimensionality (n): {{ n }}
- Average selectivity (c): {{ c_avg | round(3) }}
- **Current R̄: {{ (r_bar * 100) | round(1) }}%** in progressive interpretation

### Recognition Summary

{% if r_bar > 0.7 %}
This concept is currently in an **open/generative** interpretive mode.
{% elif r_bar < 0.3 %}
This concept is currently in a **closed/conservative** interpretive mode.
{% else %}
This concept is in a **balanced/ambiguous** interpretive mode.
{% endif %}

{% if n > 2 %}
With {{ n }} allosteric ports, this concept has high cooperativity potential — small contextual shifts may produce large interpretive changes.
{% endif %}

{# Audit log #}
{{ audit_log('recognize', concept.id, None, r_bar, 'success') }}
{{ end_span('recognize', 'success', {'r_bar': r_bar, 'n_h': hill_coefficient}) }}
{% endif %}
